# Django APIView Convention

All project-owned DRF views must subclass `rest_framework.views.APIView`.

## Rules

- Do not use `generics.*`, `ViewSet`, or `ModelViewSet` for new endpoints
- Implement HTTP verbs explicitly: `get`, `post`, `patch`, `put`, `delete`
- Use separate input and output serializers (e.g. `UserRegisterInputSerializer` / `UserOutputSerializer`)
- Set `permission_classes` on the view class

## Example

```python
class RegisterView(APIView):
    permission_classes = [permissions.AllowAny]

    def post(self, request):
        serializer = UserRegisterInputSerializer(data=request.data)
        serializer.is_valid(raise_exception=True)
        user = serializer.save()
        return Response(UserOutputSerializer(user).data, status=status.HTTP_201_CREATED)
```

## Exception

Third-party views (e.g. `TokenObtainPairView`, `TokenRefreshView` from simplejwt) may stay in `urls.py` as-is.
